This stage involves selecting the right database technology and designing an optimal schema for efficient storage and retrieval of data. üóÑÔ∏èüíæüìå Data Processing: In this stage, the stored data is transformed and cleaned to prepare it for analysis. This involves applying business rules, data validation, and data enrichment techniques. üõ†Ô∏èüßπüîçüìå Data Analysis: After processing the data, it's ready for analysis. Data analysts and data scientists use this stage to explore the data, build models, and derive insights. üìäüìàüßêüìå Data Delivery: The final stage of the pipeline is to deliver the processed and analyzed data to the end-users. This can be in the form of dashboards, reports, or APIs. üööüì§üöÄA well-designed data engineering pipeline flow can significantly enhance the efficiency and effectiveness of data-driven projects. üôåüë®‚ÄçüíªWhat other stages or challenges do you encounter when building data pipelines? post_text: Past couple months i was working at, what i can call, a "dream job", with nice people and interesting challenging tasks. But, looking at the current situation in my home country, I've decided to start looking for a job again.I am already abroad and flexible in terms of location. I don't really need help with relocation,  but i would really appreciate any help. I'm currently looking for a position in a EU based company that can give me an invitation and a work visa.What i can offer as an employee. I am a Python / JS fullstack developer with a 5+ years of experience (more details in my CV) and bunch of interesting projects i've worked in, which i can tell you more about at the interview.I can communicate with the team in English and i consider my level of English as upper intermediate. I will definitely go to language courses to learn the local language, this will help to integrate better.Looking forward to hear from you. I really hope that I will find a new team and a new home where I can work productively and be useful. Thanks for your attention and stay safe in this tough times.

Now about my skills:

- Typescript / Javascript / Angular 2+
My dashboards since 2016 powered by Angular and typescript

- NodeJS / NestJS / ExpressJS
When It possible, I'm using NestJS whithin MEAN stack, it wery clean and powerfull.

- Python / aiohttp / sqlalchemy / django
I like to create python microservices with async technologies (AIOHTTP an other). Also I can parse most of websites with help of with very powerfull Python libs and can represent its data with Django (and DRF when need) or Flask.

- Domain Driven Design and software architecture
I think that DDD is a core of successful architecture. I still cannot consider myself as a profy in DDD, but I am moving towards this day by day.

- PHP7 / Symfony
I developing apps on Symfony since 2007, from v1 up to v5. Also I likes API Platform, which helping me to create "fast and furious" microservices with PHP for last four years.
  
- C# / .Net MVC5 / .Net Core
For complex information system, like systems created for state / government needs I prefer to use .Net plaform.

- Typescript / Javascript / Angular 2+
My dashboards since 2016 powered by Angular and typescript

- NodeJS / NestJS / ExpressJS
When It possible, I'm using NestJS whithin MEAN stack, it wery clean and powerfull.

- Python / aiohttp / sqlalchemy / django
I like to create python microservices with async technologies (AIOHTTP an other). Also I can parse most of websites with help of with very powerfull Python libs and can represent its data with Django (and DRF when need) or Flask.

- Domain Driven Design and software architecture
I think that DDD is a core of successful architecture. I still cannot consider myself as a profy in DDD, but I am moving towards this day by day.

- PHP7 / Symfony
I developing apps on Symfony since 2007, from v1 up to v5. Also I likes API Platform, which helping me to create "fast and furious" microservices with PHP for last four years.
  
- C# / .Net MVC5 / .Net Core
For complex information system, like systems created for state / government needs I prefer to use .Net plaform.
